<%# ========== OFFCANVAS NAVBAR (responsive - above lg shows inline) ========== %>
<%- passData.plugin.bootstrapNavbar.render({name: 'offcanvasResponsive'}, passData) %>

<div class="container mt-4">
  <h1>Offcanvas Navbar - Responsive</h1>

  <div class="card mt-3">
    <div class="card-header">Caratteristiche di questo esempio</div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <ul>
        <li><strong>type:</strong> <code>offcanvas</code></li>
        <li><strong>bgClass:</strong> <code>bg-success</code> (verde)</li>
        <li><strong>expandAt:</strong> <code>lg</code></li>
        <li><strong>offcanvasAlways:</strong> <code>false</code> (responsive: sopra <code>lg</code> mostra navbar inline)</li>
        <li><strong>position:</strong> <code>start</code> (offcanvas da sinistra)</li>
        <li><strong>Auth:</strong> Cart e Account dropdown visibili solo per utenti autenticati, Sign In solo per non autenticati</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card mt-3">
    <div class="card-header">Differenza con Horizontal collapse</div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <p>A differenza del tipo <code>horizontal</code> che usa <code>collapse</code>, il tipo <code>offcanvas</code> mostra un pannello scorrevole laterale quando il menu viene aperto sotto il breakpoint.</p>
      <p><strong>Prova:</strong> Ridimensiona la finestra sotto <code>lg</code> e clicca il hamburger per vedere il pannello offcanvas.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card mt-3">
    <div class="card-header">Codice EJS</div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <pre><code>&lt;%- passData.plugin.bootstrapNavbar.render({name: 'offcanvasResponsive'}, passData) %&gt;</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="mt-3"><a href="/navbarExamples/">&larr; Tutti gli esempi</a></p>
</div>

